This paper discusses the development of a system for searching, constructing, exploring, and discussing web archive collections. The focus is on supporting collaborative construction and exploration of these collections. The paper also discusses the iterative evaluation-driven design-based research approach used to develop the system. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Computers and Society (cs.CY).
